Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the achievable rate of OFDM-IM with Gaussian input, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper investigates the sum rate of multi-cell OFDM-IM, which is relevant to wireless networking and cellular communication systems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of OFDM-IM in a multi-cell system, which can be viewed as a control problem in a communication network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of OFDM-IM, which is a modulation technique used in multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - Although less likely, the paper may also be relevant to the societal impact of wireless communication systems and their performance.
